le%20gains%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20providing%20a%20bit%20more%20energy%2C%20helping%20you%20push%20a%20little%20bit%20harder%20and%20work%20out%20for%20longer%20before%20getting%20tired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20bodies%20naturally%20produce%20creatine%20through%20a%20combination%20of%20amino%20acids.%20That's%20only%20a%20small%20amount%2C%20though.%20We%20can%20get%20more%20of%20it%20from%20some%20foods%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Fred-meat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ered%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fish%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20through%20supplements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20demand%20for%20creatine%20as%20a%20fitness%20aid%20has%20spiked%2C%20with%20retail%20prices%20up%20150%25%20and%20sales%20increased%20by%2090%25%20year%20over%20year%2C%20despite%20steadily%20rising%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20for%20muscle-hungry%20gym%20bros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225738%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Muscle%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685569b985e81483682c72ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223530%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECreatine%20gives%20your%20cells%20more%20energy%2C%20helping%20you%20to%20push%20a%20little%20harder%20in%20the%20gym%20before%20you%20get%20tired.%3Cp%3Egilaxia%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20men%20continue%20to%20make%20up%20the%20majority%20of%20creatine%20users%2C%20about%2021%25%20of%20the%20creatine%20buyers%20are%20women%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20nationwide%20supplement%20retailers%20The%20Vitamin%20Shoppe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20SuppCo%2C%20both%20Glen%2C%20the%20CSO%2C%20and%20Steve%20Martocci%2C%20the%20CEO%2C%20said%20their%20wives%20have%20recently%20started%20taking%20creatine%20%E2%80%94%20reflecting%20a%20broader%20trend%20of%20women%20as%20a%20growing%20consumer%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20changed%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartocci%20pointed%20to%20more%20evidence%20dispelling%20the%20myth%20that%20creatine%20is%20just%20for%20muscle%20men%20to%20bulk%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2072-6643%2F15%2F16%2F3567%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20creatine%20can%20support%20hormonal%20health%20for%20women%2C%20helping%20to%20counteract%20shifts%20that%20can%20occur%20during%20the%20menstrual%20cycle%20by%20helping%20to%20maintain%20levels%20of%20glycogen%20in%20the%20muscle%20for%20better%20energy%20and%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f485d814-927b-420c-83c8-ed0f2b157411%5C%22%3ECreatine%20slows%20aging%20and%20boosts%20brain%20health%2C%20per%20new%20research%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20a%20small%20study%20found%20that%20patients%20with%20Alzheimer's%20disease%20saw%20a%20boost%20to%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-ages-more-57-70-78-protein-exercise-sleep-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecognitive%20function%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20supplementing%20creatine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20that%20just%20providing%20more%20energy%20to%20the%20brain%20could%20be%20useful%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Forbes%2C%20a%20sports%20science%20researcher%20and%20professor%20at%20Brandon%20University%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20brain%20actually%20uses%20about%2020%25%20of%20your%20total%20energy%20expenditure%2C%20even%20though%20it%20only%20weighs%20about%202%25%20of%20your%20body%20weight.%20So%20for%20a%20tissue%2C%20it's%20very%20energetically%20demanding%2C%26quot%3B%20Forbes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22brain%20scan%20alzheimer's%20dementia%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f208e2c3f73703591325a4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20a%20small%2C%20buzzy%20study%2C%20creatine%20boosted%20cognitive%20function%20in%20people%20with%20Alzheimer's%3Cp%3EWestend61%2F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECreatine%20also%20seems%20to%20have%20an%20anti-inflammatory%20effect%2C%20making%20the%20brain%20more%20resilient%20against%20stresses%20that%20would%20wear%20down%20its%20ability%20to%20perform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20too%20much%20inflammation%20or%20too%20much%20oxidative%20stress%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20poor%20cognition%20or%20poor%20brain%20functions%2C%26quot%3B%20Forbes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20recent%20studies%20have%20found%20that%20supplementing%20creatine%20could%20also%20help%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-that-age-you-faster-make-you-look-older-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emitigate%20the%20effects%20of%20aging%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20concussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20theory%20is%20that%20the%20brain%20can%20remodel%20itself%20or%20at%20least%20maintain%20its%20function%20during%20times%20of%20stress%2C%26quot%3B%20Candow%2C%20the%20aging%20researcher%20at%20Regina%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20anybody%20in%20the%20world%20that's%20not%20stressed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20research%20is%20expanding%20creatine's%20reach%20to%20consumers%20beyond%20the%20gym%2C%20according%20to%20Muriel%20Gonzalez%2C%20president%20of%20nationwide%20supplement%20retailer%20The%20Vitamin%20Shoppe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCreatine%20is%20undergoing%20a%20major%20transformation%20%E2%80%94%20from%20a%20niche%20sports%20nutrition%20supplement%20to%20a%20versatile%20tool%20for%20daily%20health%20and%20longevity%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20told%20Business%20Insider%20over%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETotal%20creatine%20sales%20have%20spiked%20by%20300%25%20from%202019%20to%202024%20at%20The%20Vitamin%20Shoppe%2C%20and%20are%20continuing%20to%20